name: Private Suite Near It All
description:
A full suite including private bathroom, queen bed, sitting area, full flat screen TV, Apple TV, DVD player, microwave, plates, cutlery. All of this in a historic Victorian with modern eclectic styling.

The space
Our home is on the historic register for Los Angeles. Built in 1905, it has been totally renovated. We love our amazing home and have decorated it with accents from our travels, passions, and experiences.

We look forward to sharing our place with you.

Guest access
You will have access to your suite which includes your own bathroom, microwave, mini fridge, and Apple TV. You will also find a coffee and tea station with the fixings for French press coffee and teas. You do not have access to the kitchen nor the laundry. If you stay longer than a week then you will have access to the laundry. Our kittens are only allowed in the kitchen and their room. Please respect this.

We also provide access to a common
neighborhood_overview:
We are walking distance from USC and St. Mary's College. Our area is fantastically eclectic. Entire sections of historic and gorgeous homes next to apartments next to more modern buildings.

You'll find great fare like at 23rd St. Cafe which is a fusion of Mexican, Asian, and American foods as well as standards like Grinder Diner (very old school), and new experiences like Italian tapas at Bacaro LA or Korean and Japanese tapas at Ebaes.

Great coffee can be found at 23rd St. Cafe as well as at Nature's Brew (which also has a fantastic bakery and amazing lunch and brunch menu). A quick search on Yelp will reveal even more treasures. And don't forget to check out our guidebook. We update it with the faves from our own wanderings as well as recommendations from other travelers.

We are walking distance (a few miles) from the Rose Garden, the California African American Museum, The California Science Museum and much more!
host_about:
Things I cannot live without:
1. my husband
2. air
3. water
4. friends
5. music
6. laughter
7.  joy
8. great stories
9. happiness
10. experiencing different cultures and communities.  The world is so big, why not get to know it? 
 
Favorite destinations: Paris, Barcelona, Seattle, San Francisco, New York, Venice.

We have two cats who are incredibly friendly. They have access to the common areas but not the suites.

I'm a writer.  I adore traveling, writing, reading, a great workout and spending time with friends and family.  

In terms of hosting, we are laid back. We love meeting new people and enjoy quiet time. Our home is conveniently in a quiet area yet within walking distance of USC, the Los Angeles Convention Center, LA Live, and within quick driving distance to Hollywood, Beverly Hills, Studio City, Echo Park, Los Feliz, Burbank, and Santa Monica. This is one of the main reasons we chose to live where we do - we can have the best of it all. 

Our common room is full of books and magazines. Guess what? You are free to take a copy.  You are also welcomed to leave a book or magazine that you really enjoyed. I'm sure another guest would love to read it too.

If you are staying with us for a week or more, then we provide access to a washer and dryer. Always nice to have clean clothes on long journeys.

Please know that we are very responsive. If you have a question or can't find something or what-have-you then we answer quickly. We want to be sure your stay is a great one.
